headline: UnitedHealth Group Stock Rises on Earnings. Here’s Why.
summary: Shares of  UnitedHealth Group  gained in premarket trading Tuesday after the healthcare giant posted better-than-expected third-quarter earnings and hiked its full-year guidance.  Adjusted earnings of $2.92 a share surpassed the $2.80 analysts had forecast, according to FactSet.  The company raised its full-year adjusted earnings outlook to at least $16.25 a share, up from at least $16 previously.

headline: Scott Foster, CPA, MBA, Joins Sightview as Chief Financial Officer
summary: DURHAM, N.C., October 28, 2025--Sightview, the only electronic health record and practice management partner focused solely on eyecare, has appointed D. Scott Foster (Scott), CPA, MBA, as chief financial officer. With more than thirty years of experience in healthcare finance, Scott joins Sightview as the organization continues to reshape itself for the future of eyecare.
